I will set your mother on fire.

174
00:15:37,052 --> 00:15:38,747
Oh, it's no use.

175
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:55,929
With this hand,
I will lift your sorrows.

176
00:15:56,105 --> 00:16:00,769
Your cup will never empty,
for I will be your wine.

177
00:16:02,478 --> 00:16:03,740
Mrs. Everglot.

178
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:06,610
You look ravishing this evening.

179
00:16:07,449 --> 00:16:12,546
What's that, Mr. Everglot?
Call you "Dad"? If you insist, sir.

180
00:16:12,721 --> 00:16:17,215
With this candle,
I will light your way in darkness.

181
00:16:17,726 --> 00:16:19,387
With this ring...

182
00:16:20,162 --> 00:16:23,757
...I ask you to be mine.

183
00:17:17,219 --> 00:17:18,413
I do.

184
00:18:47,075 --> 00:18:50,044
You may kiss the bride.

185
00:18:57,085 --> 00:19:00,248
- A new arrival.
- He must've fainted.

186
00:19:00,422 --> 00:19:03,220
- Are you all right?
- What..? What happened?

187
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:06,452
By Jove, man. Looks like
we've got ourselves a breather.

188
00:19:06,895 --> 00:19:09,762
- Does he have a dead brother?
- He's still soft.

189
00:19:12,768 --> 00:19:14,395
A toast, then.

190
00:19:20,108 --> 00:19:21,700
To the newlyweds.

191
00:19:21,877 --> 00:19:23,105
Newlyweds?

192
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:28,175
In the woods,
you said your vows so perfectly.

193
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:29,942
I did?

194
00:19:30,118 --> 00:19:31,551
I did.

195
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:33,950
Wake up! Wake up! Wake up!

196
